# Frontend Testing

## Stack

- **Runner:** Jest 29 with `ts-jest` preset
- **Environment:** `jsdom` (configured in `client/jest.config.cjs`)
- **Component testing:** Enzyme 2 with `shallow` renderer and `react-addons-test-utils` (React 15 compatible)
- **Fetch mock:** `client/jest.setup.js` assigns a custom mock from `tests/__tests__/fetch-mock.js` to `global.fetch`

## Config files

- `client/jest.config.cjs` — Jest configuration (CommonJS module)
- `client/jest.setup.js` — Runs before tests; sets up the fetch mock

## Existing test files

- `tests/__tests__/util.test.tsx` — Tests for `url()` and `submitForm()` utility functions
- `tests/components/form/__tests__/Input.test.tsx` — Tests for `Input` component rendering and validation
- `tests/components/form/__tests__/Constraints.test.tsx` — Tests for constraint validation helpers

## Conventions

- Place test files in `__tests__/` directories adjacent to the code they test
- Use Enzyme `shallow()` for component rendering (not `mount()` — avoids full DOM)
- Mock `fetch` via the global setup; do not import `jest` directly in test files
- Run tests: `cd client && npm test`
